sentences: Baluan Sholak (Kazakh: Балуан Шолақ, Balýan Sholaq; 1864–1919), was a Kazakh Turkic composer, singer, poet, dombra player, dzhigit and wrestler.
Baluan Sholak was born on 11 December 1864, in the village of Karaotkel near the Khan mountains in modern Akmola Province, Kazakhstan, and was named Nurmagambetov.
Some of his songs became very popular in Kazakhstan, including Галия (Galia) and Сентябрь (September).
His songs are still heard today, and the Baluan Sholak Palace of Culture and Sports in Almaty, built in 1967 and seating 5000, is named in his honour.
